 style="border-top: 1px solid; margin: 0 0 24px 0;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p style="line-height: normal; margin: 12px 0 0 0; color: inherit; text-decoration: none; font-size: 14px !important;"&gt;彭博社观点&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2 style="line-height: normal; font-weight: 700; margin: 12px 0 0 0; font-size: 20px !important;"&gt;特朗普在伊朗战争中使用了错误的油价&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p style="line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0 0 0; color: inherit; text-decoration: none; font-size: 16px !important;"&gt;哈维尔·布拉斯写道，特朗普已将西德克萨斯中质原油价格转变为一场关于战争的公投。但对经济来说重要的不是 WTI 的价格，而是精炼石油产品的成本。而且还在迅速上升。 &lt;/p&gt;&lt;div style="display: block; width: 100%; height: 40px; text-align: center; line-height: 40px; border: 1px solid; border-radius: 8px; margin: 16px 0 0 0; font-size: 14px !important;"&gt;阅读更多&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="border-top: 1px solid; margin: 24px 0 0 0;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p style="margin-top: 24px; font-size: 16px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div style="margin-top: 24px;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://links.message.bloomberg.com/a/sc/KVtzJ3yqPtpcWEk0r8BdtsOokQKjFMvFVj_pV9dyWnHGFYtTfnzJalaZKlWgfmYKOQMDORz83bBV4M3KohWgG76nizZlwTJ5Xy3Vw__VQzYN7W5CGyLWTNkT6PSCgd4FoHL8e4jhTVWBCYfqojW8hDFMaJLtDav-SXPv5_HVAVtsd39MQf7-XC_rjMv0ZkRZBAOAeL-I0CMNKMggQGF0aMxleHqPzOnbav_NPVx6IuQexLSQ4Tc2jn6rhzBxSAbNT4MmgnvQdO4CB4u39qHLuTo5TUz-hVQhOU3gLuFjAVDmeLb5Qa67KMk4RUIh2LW7FfTJlwCk8m2k9a7zxz-kPC7tLZ-uth727FDbpJGUvyX6Q7R_aoFk0m4VN7xD8tohfOSv4Ek/qtPMbJqkH0Xpj9BZlSplWaUt6rrJqKyA/18" style="font-size: inherit; color: inherit; text-decoration: none;" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;!--[if mso]&gt;&lt;table width="580"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src="https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/idCjE.CfmVsM/v1/-1x-1.jpg" alt="Unemployed Americans line up as they wait to gain entry to meet prospective employers at the Los Angeles Career Fair on March 23, 2010. US Treasury Secretary Timothy Geithner has recently warned jobless Americans they face a torrid year ahead, predicting continued high unemployment levels despite advances &amp;quot;sometime this spring.&amp;quot; Speaking in Congress, Geithner said some improvements in the decimated US job market would come soon, but not enough to eat into the near double-digit unemployment that has brought the crisis into ordinary Americans' homes. He warned that more than 100,000 jobs need to be created each month to push the jobless rate down from its current level of 9.7 percent. AFP PHOTO/Mark RALSTON (Photo credit should read MARK RALSTON/AFP via Getty Images)" width="580"/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;div style="display:none"&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;img alt="2010 年 3 月 23 日，失业的美国人在洛杉矶招聘会上排队等待与未来的雇主会面。美国财政部长蒂莫西·盖特纳 (Timothy Geithner) 最近警告失业的美国人，他们将面临艰难的一年，并预测尽管“今年春天的某个时候”失业率有所提高，但失业率仍将居高不下。盖特纳在国会发表讲话时表示，遭受重创的美国就业市场很快就会出现一些改善，但还不足以消除导致危机波及普通美国家庭的接近两位数的失业率。他警告说，每月需要创造超过10万个就业岗位，才能将失业率从目前的9.7%水平降低。法新社照片/Mark RALSTON（照片来源应为 MARK RALSTON/AFP via Getty Images）" src="https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/idCjE.CfmVsM/v1/-1x-1.jpg" style="width: 100%; display: block;" /&gt;&lt;!--[if mso]&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p style="line-height: normal; margin: 12px 0 0 0; color: inherit; text-decoration: none; font-size: 14px !important;"&gt;特朗普经济学&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2 style="line-height: normal; font-weight: 700; margin: 12px 0 0 0; font-size: 20px !important;"&gt;人工智能的诞生是为了取代你，而不是帮助你&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p style="line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0 0 0; color: inherit; text-decoration: none; font-size: 16px !important;"&gt;诺贝尔经济学奖获得者达伦·阿西莫格鲁 (Daron Acemoglu) 解释了人工智能如何&lt;em style="font-size: inherit; color: inherit; text-decoration: none;"&gt;真正&lt;/em&gt;改变工作的未来，以及对社会和民主的影响。 &lt;/p&gt;&lt;div style="display: block; width: 100%; height: 40px; text-align: center; line-height: 40px; border: 1px solid; border-radius: 8px; margin: 16px 0 0 0; font-size: 14px !important;"&gt;收听播客&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="border-top: 1px solid; margin: 24px 0 0 0;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p style="margin-top: 24px; font-size: 16px;"&gt;自伊朗战争爆发以来，&lt;stro